The paper discusses the integration of blockchain technology with existing data management systems, which falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also addresses security concerns and consensus mechanisms, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses throughput and recovery mechanisms, which are relevant to the sub-categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE).
